Patch summary:
Complete OpenGL ES 3.2 support in the Bazel-built gfxstream backend and guest
encoder. The host advertises ANDROID_EMU_gles_max_version_3_2 only when it can
create an ES 3.2 context; cube-map-array textures, sRGB decode parameters, and
valid ES 3.2 sampler units are tracked through the guest encoder. Desktop
OpenGL 4.6 maps to ES 3.2, while native EGL probes ES 3.2 before falling back.

